abstract: House Democrats on Tuesday unveiled two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump that will serve as the basis for action by the House Judiciary Committee. One accuses Trump of abuse of power, and the other accuses him of obstruction of Congress.
snippet: House Democrats on Tuesday unveiled two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump that will serve as the basis for action by the House Judiciary Committee. One accuses Trump of abuse of power, and the other accuses him of obstruction ...
lead_paragraph: House Democrats on Tuesday unveiled two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump that will serve as the basis for action by the House Judiciary Committee. One accuses Trump of abuse of power, and the other accuses him of obstruction of Congress.
headline_main: READ: Articles of Impeachment Against President Donald Trump
headline_print_headline: READ: Articles of Impeachment Against President Donald Trump

abstract: The study was an accident. The results show the positive effects of health insurance.
snippet: The study was an accident. The results show the positive effects of health insurance.
lead_paragraph: Three years ago, 3.9 million Americans received a plain-looking envelope from the Internal Revenue Service. Inside was a letter stating that they had recently paid a fine for not carrying health insurance and suggesting possible ways to enroll in coverage.

abstract: President Donald Trump warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections in talks with Russia's top diplomat on Tuesday, the White House said, after meetings where the two sides made no visible progress on nuclear arms control.
snippet: President Donald Trump warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections in talks with Russia's top diplomat on Tuesday, the White House said, after meetings where the two sides made no visible progress on nuclear arms control.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections in talks with Russia's top diplomat on Tuesday, the White House said, after meetings where the two sides made no visible progress on nuclear arms control.
headline_main: Trump Warns Russia Not to Meddle in U.S. Elections: White House
headline_print_headline: Trump Warns Russia Not to Meddle in U.S. Elections: White House

abstract: Alberto Fernandez has pulled off something of a coup. The fixer and confidante of presidents, little known outside Argentine political circles just half a year ago, took on the top job in Latin American's No. 3 economy on Tuesday.
snippet: Alberto Fernandez has pulled off something of a coup. The fixer and confidante of presidents, little known outside Argentine political circles just half a year ago, took on the top job in Latin American's No. 3 economy on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES — Alberto Fernandez has pulled off something of a coup. The fixer and confidante of presidents, little known outside Argentine political circles just half a year ago, took on the top job in Latin American's No. 3 economy on Tuesday.
headline_main: Alberto Fernandez: Political Broker to Argentina's Main Man
headline_print_headline: Alberto Fernandez: Political Broker to Argentina's Main Man

abstract: In April, the man who will be Britain's finance minister in a Labour government sought to reassure the head of the country's biggest telecoms group BT that it would not feature in his sweeping nationalisation plans.
snippet: In April, the man who will be Britain's finance minister in a Labour government sought to reassure the head of the country's biggest telecoms group BT that it would not feature in his sweeping nationalisation plans.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — In April, the man who will be Britain's finance minister in a Labour government sought to reassure the head of the country's biggest telecoms group BT that it would not feature in his sweeping nationalisation plans.
headline_main: Labour's Big State Plans Spook British Business

abstract: The Supreme Court appeared likely Tuesday to rule that insurance companies can collect $12 billion from the federal government to cover their losses in the early years of the health care law championed by President Barack Obama.
snippet: The Supreme Court appeared likely Tuesday to rule that insurance companies can collect $12 billion from the federal government to cover their losses in the early years of the health care law championed by President Barack Obama.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court appeared likely Tuesday to rule that insurance companies can collect $12 billion from the federal government to cover their losses in the early years of the health care law championed by President Barack Obama.
headline_main: Justices Seem to Favor Insurers' Obamacare Claims for $12B

abstract: Ethiopia’s prime minister Abiy Ahmed warned against the “gospel of revenge and retribution” as he accepted the Nobel Prize in Oslo.
snippet: Ethiopia’s prime minister Abiy Ahmed warned against the “gospel of revenge and retribution” as he accepted the Nobel Prize in Oslo.
lead_paragraph: NAIROBI, Kenya — Ethiopia’s prime minister Abiy Ahmed warned in his speech accepting the Nobel Peace Prize in Oslo on Tuesday that social media is now being used to sow “hate and division” and undermine Ethiopia’s delicate political transition.

abstract: President Donald Trump lashed out Tuesday at FBI Director Christopher Wray, expressing dissatisfaction that Wray didn't cast a watchdog report on the origins of the Russia investigation  as devastating for the bureau.
snippet: President Donald Trump lashed out Tuesday at FBI Director Christopher Wray, expressing dissatisfaction that Wray didn't cast a watchdog report on the origins of the Russia investigation  as devastating for the bureau.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump lashed out Tuesday at FBI Director Christopher Wray, expressing dissatisfaction that Wray didn't cast a watchdog report on the origins of the Russia investigation as devastating for the bureau.
headline_main: Trump Sharply Criticizes FBI Head After Russia Probe Report
headline_print_headline: Trump Sharply Criticizes FBI Head After Russia Probe Report

abstract: U.S. Senator Chuck Grassley said on Tuesday he has been assured by the White House that 2020 biofuel blending mandates will be finalized in accordance with a September agreement between the administration and biofuel and corn producers.
snippet: U.S. Senator Chuck Grassley said on Tuesday he has been assured by the White House that 2020 biofuel blending mandates will be finalized in accordance with a September agreement between the administration and biofuel and corn producers.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Senator Chuck Grassley said on Tuesday he has been assured by the White House that 2020 biofuel blending mandates will be finalized in accordance with a September agreement between the administration and biofuel and corn producers.
headline_main: Senator Grassley Says White House Assured Him on 2020 Biofuels Plan
headline_print_headline: Senator Grassley Says White House Assured Him on 2020 Biofuels Plan

abstract: The strikes in French cities would continue indefinitely unless the government changes direction in its effort to overhaul the pension system, a labor leader said.
